{
  "texts": [
    "The widespread use of glass underscores the urgent need to improve recycling practices.",
    "By enhancing glass recycling rates, we can greatly reduce its environmental impact, conserve natural resources, and decrease the energy required to produce new glass [41].",
    "SCBASCBA is a by-product of the sugarcane industry, primarily produced from burning bagasse during sugar production.",
    "The process starts with crushing sugarcane and extracting the juice through milling.",
    "The fibrous residue left after juice extraction, called bagasse, is often used as a biofuel to power boilers in sugar mills."
  ]
}